For the following excerpt, provide the GKC-CI annotation of 'Attribute': ['Content Posting Agreement and the Use of Copyrighted Content

By posting User Generated Content on Packback, you agree to the Content Posting Agreement as outlined here:

You assert that you are not posting Copyrighted Content without proper licensing for sharing, distributing or otherwise remixing;
If you share content with a Creative Commons License, you agree to provide proper attribution as the "Source" when posting;
You will not post inflammatory, inappropriate, derogatory, or otherwise egregious content that limits or detracts from other users' ability to have a safe and professional educational environment on the platform.']

For the following excerpt, provide the GKC-CI annotation of 'Aim': ['We target (and measure the performance of) ads to Members, Visitors and others both on and off our Services directly or through a variety of partners, using the following data, whether separately or combined:

Data from advertising technologies on and off our Services, pixels, ad tags, cookies, and device identifiers;
Member-provided information (e.g., profile, contact information, title and industry);
Data from your use of our Services (e.g., search history, feed, content you read, who you follow or is following you, connections, groups participation, page visits, videos you watch, clicking on an ad, etc.']

For the following excerpt, provide the GKC-CI annotation of 'Aim': ['Use of Subscriber Information and User Generated Content
Use of Subscriber Information

Packback collects and uses the above outlined subscriber information to:

Create and manage your membership account;
Process your transactions;
Provide customer service;
Perform research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services, curriculum, educational outcomes, and technologies;
To display content that is customized to your preferences;
If you are a forum contributor on Packback Questions, to identify your uploaded content as your own authenticated content for the purposes of tracking your usage for grading purposes; and,
If you are an employee, contractor, or paid contributor for Packback, to compensate you and to prepare tax information slips; and,
To communicate with you about your transactions, new products and services.']

